    <p itemprop="text">
      QUETTA, Pakistan (AP) — Gunmen in southwestern Pakistan killed at least 38 people in three separate attacks on Monday, officials said, while the military said security forces killed 21 insurgents, marking one of the deadliest days of violence in the restive Baluchistan province, with reports of othe
      <a itemprop="url" href="/world/2024/08/26/gunmen-kill-23-passengers-taken-from-vehicles-in-an-attack-in-southwest-pakistan/"  >(ABDUL SATTAR and MUNIR AHMED, Associated Press, WGN 9)</a>
